&lt;h2 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link"&gt;&amp;para;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Since a couple of weeks I noticed that my Time Machine did not backup. I observed that this began more or less the same time when I had rebuilt my Spotlight index, because I had some problems with Spotlight that keeps on indexing …&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Peter Florijn</dc:creator><pubDate>Mon, 25 Aug 2014 09:36:29 +0200</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blog.florijnconsultancy.nl,2014-08-25:/articles/slow-time-machine-backup-on-mavericks.html</guid><category>articles</category></item><item><title>Reset fritz! powerline 520e</title><link>https://blog.florijnconsultancy.nl/articles/reset-fritz-powerline-520e.html</link><description>&lt;h1 id="introduction"&gt;Introduction&lt;a class="headerlink" href="#introduction" title="Permanent link"&gt;&amp;para;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sometimes I do not get connection to my FritzBox. After some investigation I found out that this was caused by one of my Powerline 520 E adapters. It was not working as expected, although the &lt;span class="caps"&gt;LED&lt;/span&gt;&amp;rsquo;s were suggesting&amp;nbsp;otherwise&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;I installed the Fritz! Powerline application on my &lt;span class="caps"&gt;OSX …&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description><dc:creator xmlns:dc="http://purl.org/dc/elements/1.1/">Peter Florijn</dc:creator><pubDate>Sun, 24 Aug 2014 08:38:14 +0200</pubDate><guid isPermaLink="false">tag:blog.florijnconsultancy.nl,2014-08-24:/articles/reset-fritz-powerline-520e.html</guid><category>articles</category></item><item><title>Non-standard service request workflow</title><link>https://blog.florijnconsultancy.nl/articles/non-standard-service-request-workflow.html</link><description>&lt;hr&gt;
